<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 06 at 2:59PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Marion
and southwestern Taylor Counties through 330 PM EDT...
At 258 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Charing, or 10 miles
southwest of Butler. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Butler, Rupert, Charing, Howard and Mauk.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
